# UI/UX Design Rules

## Navigation

- **Use a left-side navigation panel** for multi-page apps
- Show clear labels or links for each app page
- Keep the navigation always visible (not hidden behind hamburger on desktop)
- Use contrasting colors between the navigation panel and the main content area
- Place the logout option at the bottom of the navigation panel

## Page Layout

- Show a clear page title at the top of each screen
- Keep spacing, padding, and alignment consistent across all pages
- Maintain enough white space to avoid clutter
- Make the layout responsive for desktop, tablet, and mobile
- Keep each screen focused on one main action

## Interactive Elements

- Make buttons visually distinct from text links
- Add hover and active states to all interactive elements
- Use consistent icon sizes and styles
- Show clear success and error messages after actions

## Typography & Readability

- Use readable fonts (minimum 14–16px base size)
- Ensure sufficient color contrast for text

## Forms

- Keep forms simple and only include essential fields
- Place validation messages directly under the related field
- Group related fields together

## Data Display

- Keep charts and data easy to understand at a glance
- Put filters and search tools close to the data they affect
- Use tables for structured data with clear headers

## Organization

- Keep settings and account options grouped in a predictable place
- Use consistent patterns across similar pages

## Layout Pattern

```tsx
// Standard page layout with left sidebar
export default function Layout({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  return (
    <div className="flex min-h-screen">
      <aside className="w-64 border-r bg-muted/40 flex flex-col">
        <nav className="flex flex-col gap-2 p-4 flex-1">
          <Link href="/page1">Page 1</Link>
          <Link href="/page2">Page 2</Link>
        </nav>
        <div className="p-4 border-t">
          <LogoutButton />
        </div>
      </aside>
      <main className="flex-1 p-6">
        <h1 className="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Page Title</h1>
        {children}
      </main>
    </div>
  )
}
```

## Responsive Breakpoints

```tsx
// Mobile-first responsive pattern
<div className="flex flex-col md:flex-row min-h-screen">
  {/* Sidebar hidden on mobile, visible on tablet+ */}
  <aside className="hidden md:flex md:w-64 border-r">
    {/* Navigation */}
  </aside>
  <main className="flex-1 p-4 md:p-6">
    {children}
  </main>
</div>
```

## Spacing Standards

| Element | Tailwind Class |
|---------|---------------|
| Page padding | `p-4 md:p-6` |
| Section gap | `gap-6` or `space-y-6` |
| Card padding | `p-4` or `p-6` |
| Form field gap | `gap-4` or `space-y-4` |
| Button spacing | `gap-2` or `gap-3` |

## Button vs Link Guidelines

| Use Button | Use Link |
|-----------|----------|
| Form submissions | Page navigation |
| Actions (save, delete, submit) | Opening new pages |
| Triggering modals | External URLs |
| State changes | Breadcrumbs |
